    "narrative": "Today\u2019s optimal lineup for the Austin Waves is headlined by **Kyle Tucker**, whose 85.90 score stands as the apex of our daily projections. Facing Sugano, **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and a favorable matchup against an xERA of 4.69. He is flanked by **Gunnar Henderson** (79.59), whose elite leadoff position and strong platoon advantage against Bibee solidify his status as a must-start anchor. We are also projecting high output from **Andy Pages** (72.14) and **Josh Lowe** (71.68), both of whom capitalize on high park factors and favorable pitcher matchups to provide significant value in the outfield.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the card was pulling **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (57.57) to the bench. Despite his excellent xwOBA, the combination of a tough matchup against Soroka and the high efficiency scores of our active roster forced him out of the starting nine. Similarly, while we prioritize stolen bases, **Brady House** (47.10) was edged out despite the opportunistic stolen base profile against Webb, as the scarcity of his defensive slot relative to the rest of our high-efficiency starters made him the odd man out. \n\nInvestors should monitor the status of **Liam Hicks**, who is currently our lowest-scoring active starter at 40.68. His output is dampened by a sub-par matchup against Crow, and he represents the primary risk for a mid-game substitution if the Waves need to protect game caps. While the park factors for **Andy Pages**, **Josh Lowe**, and **Kyle Tucker** provide a robust ceiling today, the entire roster must remain disciplined against the high-velocity, elite-SP environment presented by the current schedule.",
